<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="1036" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1036">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">853.00 Revolution 1931/1: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">South</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-06T16:00:00+00:00">April 6, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:15 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. I am reliably informed Funchal, Madeira, in the hands of rebels. Have
                            not heard from Consul Huddleston. Two gunboats with troops leaving
                            Lisbon today for Madeira.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">South</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>